snippet.textDisplay:
It’s actually not that bad to clean the school. You get to talk to your friends (teachers doesn’t care how loud you are) you get to miss half of the period to clean the school. You get to chose if you want to clean your classroom floor, hallway, blackboard, or the stairs, every body gets to do every single one of them. But of course there’s limits. Also, in japan, schools doesn’t have cafeteria so they eat in their classrooms. And about 4-6 kids serve the food. Some kids bring their food from home. When it’s recess and your still eating you have to stay in for recess to finish your lunch.
Another facts: when they go on a field trip they usually take train. Or walk when it’s worth walking.
